<br>
This is an adventure and questing and item aquistition game so...  <br>
<br>
Why do vendors sell higher level spells at all?  <br>
Why are there almost no spells that are given as the rewards for quests?  <br>
Why shouldn't casters of all but the lowest levels be expected to go out and adventure to earn (directly or indirectly) their spells?<br>
<br>
When a rogue levels up he gets a few extra hps.  When a caster levels up he gets a few extra hps and the potential for a very small amount of pp to upgrade his entire lineup of spells.<br>
<br>
IMO, it is a total cop-out game design-wise for casters to be able to buy all but the most low level spells from vendors.   At the very least, questing should be required to obtain the core spells at medium and higher levels.<br>
<br>
--Benolas<br>
